> >Yes that's sure the problem. The dentries growing to crazy values is a
> 
> Forget to tell that it's not a memleak but only an unbalance in the
> icache/dcache shrinking. If you run an hog for a few seconds (just to run
> a bit into swap) the icache/dcache will be shrunk immediatly.
It's not just a .42 issue though.  I'm using 2.3.41 and to my untutored
eye it doesn't appear to shrink.
[root@wr5z /root]# cat /proc/meminfo
        total:    used:    free:  shared: buffers:  cached:
Mem:  63610880 52514816 11096064        0   499712 19607552
Swap: 73990144  2658304 71331840
and /proc/slabinfo shows:
inode_cache        46489  57576
bdev_cache            21     63
signal_queue           1     29
kiobuf                 0      0
buffer_head         8293   8400
mm_struct             26     50
vm_area_struct       479    693
dentry_cache       18799  45415
